 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uasiago.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asiago</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/24/01 12:12:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Push back spells and PB AoE</span><hr size=1> Thunderclap is the ultimate herding spell.  2 wizzies using this to herd can get every mob stuffed into a single point.  Herding really helps manage big pulls and is worthwhile to do.<br>
